cs.LO, cs.PL, cs.DC, cs.SE, cs.DS

This paper deals with abstract machines for game semantics, which is a topic related to logic and programming languages. Therefore, cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) and cs.PL (Programming Languages) are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also discusses distributed systems and networks, which could fall under cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) and cs.SE (Software Engineering). Finally, the paper introduces new abstract machines, which could be considered as a type of data structure, and thus could be relevant to cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms).
